			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: How to handle runners when kiting??<a name="42223"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 25 04 8:51 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>When the mob gets close to running HP level, drop one chant, and start doing Selos, SNARE, Chant.  So, when the mob goes into its &quot;death run&quot; it stops in its tracks.  You can keep circling in your little kite spot, and any adds you already have still can't catch you.
<br />

<br />
The other option, is to move your kiting circle as the mob runs, so he doesn't get out of range.  The problem though, as you mentioned, is that you are much more likely to get new adds that way.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Scherzo Glissando <BR>
