				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: How to handle runners when kiting??<a name="43123"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 30 04 11:08 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I wanted to thank you all again.
<br />

<br />
I got to 30 by pulling the whole camp of gnolls over and over at the spires in SK.  What a breeze. 
<br />

<br />
That is a perfect zone for kiting the whole camp.  I just pull one and than ran by others so they joined our little party.  I just kept twisting DDD and CoD.  You don't need to add Selos cause the speed and distance with just normal run speed and a few right and left turns is perfect.  When I was mixing Selos in, I ran too far from the MoBs.
<br />

<br />
I messed with Fear a bit but the feared MoBs loose their fear at different times.  I need to learn that skill. I charmed one or two as well but the charm didn't last very long.  I guess with skill ups and levels, those skills work better.
<br />

<br />
Ok, I'm 30 now and looking for a new place to hunt =).
<br />

<br />
Thanks again.
<br />

<br />
Roccka
