				<td colspan="2"><span>Just fear one at a time unless you like running away <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" /> When I'd do that I'd usually just go up to the edge of the open area with the sea to my back.  I's pull one of the cougars that path under the trees with snare all the way to the waters edge.  Typically I'd be getting a kill every 2 to 3 minutes and be able to pull non stop.  That is going to be affected by your weapons of course,  I was using a Di'zok Wristsnapper and a Sinoichie's Partisan at first.  I upgraded to a Troubadors Mace and a Fungus Cover Blade.  
<br />

<br />
When I'd charm Midnight I gave him a couple of Gnoll Hide Lariats.  Usually I'd use a SoW potion for speed and keep a Bloodstained Flute equipped and not twist,  just keep charm up on Midnight the whole time.  If he got too low on health and looked like he would die then I'd kill him myself by chanting him down.  It's great practice for when you can swarm kite later.</span></td>
