				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: How to handle runners when kiting??<a name="43246"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 31 04 1:57 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Map your &quot;Toggle Last Two Targets&quot; key.  That way, you can swap between your target and your pet (ex pet, hehe) with one keypress.
<br />

<br />
Options Window
<br />
Keyboard Tab
<br />
Target in the dropdown
<br />
Click on the spot for the key
<br />
Press your desired key to set it
<br />

<br />
If you twist with your left hand on the number row, I recommend Q.  If you are a WASD navigator, and twist with the right hand on the numpad, use one of the arithmetic operator keys (+-*/ etc.)
<br />

<br />
While you are there, set your &quot;Cycle through nearest NPCs&quot; key as well.  I put mine on Caps Lock.  This key is great for mezzing mobs in groups when they are all piled together, or you are in a hallway, and can't mouse target them.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
